they wanted them just sitting

00:37:25.507 --> 00:37:25.929
there.
 

00:37:25.929 --> 00:37:30.018
Student:  Maybe because
on a macroscopic scale opposite

00:37:30.018 --> 00:37:31.092
charges attract.
 

00:37:31.092 --> 00:37:33.871
So maybe he might not --
Prof: Yes,

00:37:33.871 --> 00:37:35.889
but that's well known,
Coulomb's law.

00:37:35.889 --> 00:37:39.889
Yes Keith -- or Kevin, right?
 

00:37:39.889 --> 00:37:41.480
Student:  If you have
them all,

00:37:41.480 --> 00:37:43.719
you have a positive sphere and
if you have the negative

00:37:43.719 --> 00:37:46.402
corpuscle inside,
then they'll cancel each other

00:37:46.402 --> 00:37:48.070
out and be a neutral body.
 

00:37:48.070 --> 00:37:50.237
Prof: Yes,
but that could be -- it

00:37:50.237 --> 00:37:53.219
wouldn't have to be a big sphere
of uniform density,

00:37:53.219 --> 00:37:55.880
you could have a little
particle of positive charge,

00:37:55.880 --> 00:37:57.269
of the same charge, right?
 

00:37:57.269 --> 00:37:58.789
It'd be the same deal.
 

00:37:58.789 --> 00:38:01.675
Student:  They didn't
know that the inverse existed,

00:38:01.675 --> 00:38:03.666
so they thought that --
Prof: No,

00:38:03.666 --> 00:38:04.539
